nib.text:
A man was arrested for allegedly fatally shooting a woman Tuesday morning in the North End, police said. 

At 3:05 a.m., a 46-year-old man called 911 and stated that he had shot his wife inside a residence on the 30 block of Winnipeg Avenue West, according to a statement from Saint Paul Police officials. 

Officers located and detained the man outside of the Ramsey County Law Enforcement Center.

Investigators responded to the residence, where they found the woman and pronounced her dead at the scene.

The suspect was then "arrested and booked into jail on suspicion of homicide", SPPD officials said. 

An investigation is ongoing. 

If you or a loved one is experiencing domestic or intimate partner violence and are in need of help or resources, visit the National Domestic Violence Hotline's website [here](https://www.thehotline.org/).
